---
title: Southern Smothered Pork Chops with Onion Gravy, Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Carrots
description: Smothering is a cooking technique that’s a staple in the American South, and for good reason—it's delicious! For this Black History Month-inspired recipe, you’ll sear juicy seasoned pork chops, then drizzle with a rich, savory onion gravy that comes together in a flash. Roasted carrots and creamy mashed potatoes complete this comforting meal.
